metadata.name: StairWaves #52
metadata.description:
StairWaves is a generative collection imagining abstract stairs built in a wavy nature, with shadows being a key theme. While some waves are quite turbulent, others are just flat.

All shapes in the artwork are built using the same core logic applied in different ways. The method used to draw the waves is also used to draw the shadows, as well as the subtle textures on the surface of the waves. This homogeneous approach ensures a consistent and flowy feel to the final output.

StairWaves is coded entirely in p5.js. 

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)

metadata.name: fxhash x thi.ng project template #124
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK (at least not intentional)!

This NFT acts as a donation/funding mechanism for a new project template Git repo, providing a compact, ready-to-go scaffolding for generative art projects aimed at the fx(hash) platform/marketplace.

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

This template evolved over time and has served as basis for some of the author's own NFT projects (https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/toxi). The template is aimed at TypeScript (but can be easily adapted to plain JavaScript) and, at the time of writing, uses Vite as dev & build tool, ensuring an altogether great & speedy workflow with minimal fuzz.

(In the future, I'm aiming to provide an alternative version for more advanced hybrid projects using TypeScript, Zig (https://ziglang.org) and WebAssembly (https://webassembly.org/)...)

Framework agnostic

Even though several packages from the https://thi.ng/umbrella ecosystem are used to provide various essential overarching functionality, the template is organized in such a way that the main parts are completely framework-agnostic. You should be able to easily plug in your own toolkit of choice, however I cannot promise to provide support for this myself (though happy to accept PRs, also in terms of further docs, how-tos, guides etc.)

Example project

A tiny, fully documented throwaway example sketch is included, illustrating the following:

- Overall project structure & build commands
- FXhash related setup
- Static & dynamic configuration and state (re)initialization (via dependency graph)
- FXhash PRNG wrapper & utilities
- Canvas & SVG conversion/export/download
- 2D geometry creation, transformation & drawing
- Basic vector algebra example usage


Keyboard shortcuts

- space :  pause/play animation
- x : download canvas as PNG
- s : download SVG version

In case of doubt, it's this example project what is used here for minting. The funding, however, will be used for the further maintenance of both this project template and supporting my other open source work. 20% are also donated to the FXhash development team itself.

Thank you for your support! üôèüòç

metadata.name: FEA #80
metadata.description:
Soft - Light - Vivid - Zen - Diverse

Feathers are unique.

They served different aspects of purposes and holds different stories of the bird.

Reimagine the formation of the feather via code.
You will see the feather hairs' growing along the spine in an animated manner.

Various patterns both from real and digital worlds were sampled.
Peacock / Dotted / Natural Graident / Digital Lerp with different color combinations.

A Special pattern called FXpunk with percentage is also introduced to pay respect to everyone@FX.

Part of the royalties to the Minter & Processing Foundation

NOTE: 
best view -> 16:9 window size in a large display. 
best view -> open Live window -> expand window size -> refresh the work
press S to export the work.

metadata.name: Love & Wild #121
metadata.description:
We often use flowers to express untold feelings towards our loved ones and most precious people in our life. But love as flowers can go wild & in unpredictable directions.

Love & Wild code come to life few weeks ago when I was alone drinking coffee at local bar, started messing with vertex Quadratic bezier and first petal appeared on screen. After few Loved flowers, the Wild ones start to emerge. Those with sharp spines that are beautiful in it‚Äôs own way but can also, like Love, inflict pain. As I was on vacation during finalising this work the colors and flavours of the Mediterranean inspired me.
But except some Wild palettes too.

Thank You

‚Äòs‚Äô for save canvas.
‚Äò2‚Äô for HD png.
‚Äò4‚Äô for 4000x4000px png.
‚Äò8‚Äô for 8000x8000px png.

Created with wild love for p5js and generative art :)
@Qotonana
July, 2022.

metadata.name: Breakers #40
metadata.description:
Companion project to Neural Collapse (#15780), for the collectors of my previous efforts.
A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple dynamic structure, this time inside a cylinder.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.

Interactivity : 
- You can click on each individual breaker to open or close them. The problem is it will toggle others.
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint. The previous interaction not being disabled while doing that, you get some switching all over the place as a bonus bug/feature.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. If you don't like jaggies and your machine can take it.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

metadata.name: Animandals #10
metadata.description:
Inspired by the Australian Aboriginal technique of pointillism, these mandalas represent the cosmos metaphysically or symbolically; a time-microcosm of the universe, but it originally meant to represent wholeness and a model for the organizational structure of life itself, a cosmic diagram that shows the relation to the infinite and the world that extends beyond and within mind & body.
In native cultures, each animal brings with it a medicine, a message or important information.
Different animal guides, also called spirit guides or power animals, come in and out of our lives depending on the direction that we are headed and the tasks that need to be completed along our journey.
I hope this Animandal brings you the energy and information you need for this time in your life.

Software used: PROCREATE
Code: @fipiaggio
Music: @8_lamat

attributes.name: Description
attributes.value: The protector and symbolizes physical strength and leadership

metadata.name: Gestalt #859
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

Controls:
‚Ä¢ Left-click/tap reassembles the piece with one less element each time
‚Ä¢ 'R' reassembles the piece with all elements
‚Ä¢ 'S' saves the output
